description: Break a PRD into vertical-slice GitHub issues (tracer bullets, HITL/AFK). Use when converting a PRD to tickets, implementation issues, or work breakdown.
alwaysApply: false
---

## PRD TO ISSUES — WORKFLOW

### Locate the PRD
- Ask for the PRD GitHub issue number or URL.
- If not in context, fetch via **GitHub MCP** (preferred) or `gh issue view <n>` including comments.

### Explore the codebase (optional)
- If needed, explore the repo to ground slices in reality.

### Draft vertical slices
- Each issue is a **thin vertical slice** through all layers end-to-end (schema, API, UI, tests) — **not** a horizontal layer-only task.
- Slices may be **HITL** (needs human decision/review) or **AFK** (agent can implement without blocking human steps). Prefer AFK when safe.
- Each completed slice is demoable or verifiable alone. Prefer many thin slices over few thick ones.

### Quiz the user
- Present a numbered list. Per slice: **Title**, **Type** (HITL/AFK), **Blocked by** (other slices), **User stories covered** (from PRD).
- Ask: granularity OK? Dependencies correct? Merge/split? HITL/AFK labels right? Iterate until approved.

### Create GitHub issues
- Create via **GitHub MCP** in dependency order (blockers first) so real issue numbers appear in "Blocked by".
- **Do not** close or modify the parent PRD issue.

### Issue body template

```text
## Parent PRD
#<parent-issue-number>

## What to build
(End-to-end behavior for this slice. Point to PRD sections; do not paste the whole PRD.)

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2
- [ ] Criterion 3

## Blocked by
- #<issue> (or "None — can start immediately")

## User stories addressed
- User story N from parent PRD
```

## PROJECT ALIGNMENT
- In-repo task tracking may also use **TODOS.md** (docs.mdc). GitHub issues remain the source for cross-repo collaboration when used.
